<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1901-07-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1901-07-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="515" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d515">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hill</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Russell</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-07-27"><hi rend="italic">July 27,
                                1901</hi>.</date></dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 432.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                            No. 643, of the 14th instant, inclosing copy of your note to the
                            Venezuelan foreign office explaining the visit of the <hi rend="italic">Mayflower</hi> to Margarita Island, and a copy of the foreign
                            office’s reply.</p>
                        <p>The incident appears thus to have been satisfactorily closed.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">David J. Hill</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>